9:
Tracking down a specific world is no
easy task, it seems.
27: The heck's goin' on over there?
30:
This is a state of emergency! The
ship that just pulled in was attacked
by monsters!
31:
Get the doctors over stat! I want all
first aid we have on deck!
34:
Damn it... It hurts! I can't take the
pain!
36: I need sedatives over here! Hurry!
47:
I may not be capable of miracles,
but I will lend my aid however I can!
51:
We won't just stand by either! Stella,
after me!
54:
Nimbus! We can carry the injured off
the ship!
66:
The doctors were quite impressed
with your healing abilities. Thanks to
your efforts, no one died today.
74:
Good work out there. You really
pulled it together, despite how down
you were earlier.
81:
Uh, maybe I read you wrong? It's
just... You gave this big sigh when we
failed at finding you a way home
today.
84:
So that is where the confusion
stems from. My apologies, but that
sigh was regarding another matter.
85:
It is something I have been mulling
over for a while, and my frustrations
must have seeped out.
88:
I am sorry my childlike behavior has
caused you concern.
94:
No apologies needed, but... perhaps
you could share what you're worried
about? We might be able to help.
97:
Very well. I shall confide in you, if you
truly do not mind.
101:
You see, I have been debating what
to do...
114:
Ah, forgive me. Explanations are in
order.
117:
I want a way to reward my lord for
working so hard every day.
119:
The solution I came up with was a
stamp system. For every task he
completes, he earns a stamp on a
card.
127:
The problem is... I am unsure what
exactly his prize should be once he
fills in a card.
130:
What kind of reward would you like if
you were in my lord's shoes?
140:
Sheesh... You'd think finding a way
home would take priority, but it's a
present that's got you wound up...
141:
Don't you wanna go back to
Landosol?
147:
But my duty is to guide my lord. I
belong at his side, no matter where
he is.
148:
I am happy to live in any world, so
long as he is in it.
153:
Huh. You know what... You've got
more spunk than people twice your
size.
158:
That's how much he means to you. I
respect that.
166:
But I hold Miss Pecorine and Miss
Karyl dear to my heart too, as well
as my other friends...
167:
You are all irreplaceable people who
I care for very deeply and am
honored to call my friends.
172:
I, too, am honored to call you my
friend.
175:
Hey there, little miss! Good thing we
caught you and your friends before
you left!
177:
Thanks for all your help! I don't even
wanna think about what woulda
happened if you hadn't stepped in!
179:
It ain't much, but please, take this as
a show of our appreciation! I swear,
nothing's fresher and tastier than
this!
187:
Wow, we can make a full-course
seafood dinner outta this!
190:
In which case... I will have to
carefully extract every bone so that
my lord will not choke!
195:
Ain't that nice? You get to pamper
your man tonight.
201:
To be blessed with my lord and
surrounded by so many wonderful
friends...
